<statement>
<p>What is the solution to <m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{3}={6}{x}+{7}</m>? <input type="text" style="width:4.6ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/> Â  </p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>2</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{3}={6}{x}+{7}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{3}-{7}={6}{x}+{7}-{7}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}-{4}={6}{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}-{4}-{8}{x}={6}{x}-{8}{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}=-{2}{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{4}}{{-{{2}}}}=\frac{{-{2}{x}}}{{-{{2}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}={x}</m>.</p>

</solution>
